Package org.openbel.framework.common

Top-level package of the BEL framework's common module.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
MapFunction<K,V> Interface defining a function that can be applied over every entry within a map.
Reportable Interface for warning/error reporting.
 

Class Summary
BELUtilities Utility methods used throughout the BEL codebase.
DBConstants BEL framework database constants.
DownloadConstants  
PathConstants BEL path constants.
SimpleOutput Prints errors and warnings via direct hand-off to the underlying streams.
Strings This class defines the set of strings used throughout BEL.
 

Exception Summary
AnnotationDefinitionResolutionException AnnotationDefinitionResolutionException encapsulates a BELWarningException designating an error in resolving an annotation definition.
BELErrorException A class of BEL user-facing exceptions considered errors.
BELException BEL base class for checked exceptions.
BELFatalException A class of BEL user-facing exceptions considered fatal.
BELRuntimeException BEL unchecked runtime exception generated by the BEL Framework.
BELUncheckedException BEL base class for unchecked exceptions generated by the framework.
BELWarningException A class of BEL user-facing exceptions considered warnings.
DBConnectionFailure DBConnectionFailure represents a fatal exception when a connection cannot be made to either the DocStore or KAMStore.
InvalidArgument BEL runtime exception indicating an invalid argument was provided.
MissingAlgorithmException MissingAlgorithmException defines a unchecked exception that represents an algorithm not available in the current environment.
MissingEncodingException MissingEncodingException defines a unchecked exception that represents a character encoding not available in the current environment.
UserFacingUncheckedException A user-facing unchecked BEL exception, requiring user-facing messages.
 

Package org.openbel.framework.common Description

Top-level package of the BEL framework's common module.
